niversary  The first ever gathering uniting VMI Christian alumni from multiple classes Inspirational speakers who have preached the gospel to the Corps of Cadets Gifted musicians and recording artists who have had a heart for VMI Prayer and Intercession for the Corps of Cadets and the Institute Opportunities for fellowship  mentoring and networking among VMI graduates Small group sessions led by VMI graduates with ministry experience in missions  evangelism  church planting  military chaplaincy and discipleship  Mark your calendar and plan to be part of this significant ministry event  Hotel group rates available at  Holiday Inn Express Lexington  540 463 7351 Best Western Plus Inn at Hunt Ridge  540 464 1500  More lodging information CH  Maj  John Casper  04   casperjp vmi edu Mrs  Patricia Mountain   mountainpm vmi edu Related Information Chaplain s Office Chaplain James Park Assoc  Chaplain John Casper  04   50th Anniversary of Ministry to the Corps Mary Cannon Secretary to the Chaplain Old Hospital Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7390 F   540  464 7727      50th Anniversary of Ministry to the Corps Sacred Assembly Celebration   January 23 25  2015 An endowment established by the late John M  Camp  Jr  40 in honor of his father  John M  Camp  05  created the position of the Chaplain to the Corps of Cadets in the fall semester of 1964  Since that time three Chaplains  CH  CAPT  Robert Wilson  USN  Ret  1964   1979  CH  COL  Charles Caudill  USAF  Ret  1979 1994  and CH  COL  James Park  USAR  Ret  1994 to present  have served in this position  In January 2014 an endowed gift given by Mr  Richard L  Goodall  66 created a position for an Associate Chaplain to the Corps of Cadets  CH  Maj  John Casper  04 was selected to fill that position  For fifty years the Corps of Cadets  its graduates and the VMI community have benefited from the caring  supportive  God honoring service of Chaplains  A Sacred Assembly scheduled for January 23 25  2